ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices
public class ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestList_ResponseMessage
extends java.lang.Object

A response message to the ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestListBroadcastIntent sent by a provider on the ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestListBroadcastIntent.PARAM_msgrDEVLISTRECEIVER. This response can be sent any time after the broadcast intent is received; the requester is responsible to ignore it if it no longer needs it.

Constant Field Values

PARAM_intREQID

public static final java.lang.String PARAM_intREQID
Key to the REQID. The REQID is an integer token identified with the originating request, it is used to associate requests with responses. This REQID must match the REQID in the ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestListBroadcastIntent this message is responding to.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

PARAM_long_array_DEVICEUID

public static final java.lang.String PARAM_long_array_DEVICEUID
Key to an array of provider specific IDs uniquely identifying a device within a provider's domain. These IDs do not have to be related to the ANT channel device IDs but are used for the purpose of communicating requests and info about this specific device between the provider and the client in future messages. Note: When the provider wishes to make available one or more devices to the client to connect to, the information pertaining to those devices is passed in these arrays. All the arrays should have the information for a given device in matching indices and thus should all be of the same length.

PARAM_string_array_DEVICEDISPLAYINFO

public static final java.lang.String PARAM_string_array_DEVICEDISPLAYINFO
Key to an array of display friendly text information for each device. The display text may be used by the client if they have space to display more text to help the user know more information about the device. Note: When the provider wishes to make available one or more devices to the client to connect to, the information pertaining to those devices is passed in these arrays. All the arrays should have the information for a given device in matching indices and thus should all be of the same length.

whatLISTRESPONSE

public static final int whatLISTRESPONSE
The what code indicating this message contains a list of identifying information of the device(s) the provider is willing to grant access to the client. The LISTRESPONSE message should always include a list of one or more devices available for use matching the original request. It should not be sent if the provider has no devices to provide. This message is sent on the ThirdPartyDeviceProviderMsgDefines.RequestForDevices.RequestListBroadcastIntent.PARAM_msgrDEVLISTRECEIVER messenger.
